
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hcitool` baraye config kardan etesalat Bluetooth dar Linux estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad device-haye Bluetooth ra peyda konid, be anha vasl shavid, va etela'at-e Bluetooth ra bebinid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hcitool dev`     --> 💻 Namayesh device-haye Bluetooth-e mojood
    🔹 `hcitool scan`    --> 📡 Scan kardan baraye device-haye Bluetooth-e nazdik
    🔹 `hcitool info <address>` --> ℹ️  Namayesh etela'at dar mored yek device Bluetooth (address-e aan ra bayad vared konid)
    🔹 `hcitool con`     --> 🔗 Namayesh etesalat-e fa'al-e Bluetooth
    🔹 `hcitool disconnect <address>` --> قطع  Disconnect kardan yek etesal Bluetooth

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hcitool dev

    🔹 Namayesh device-haye Bluetooth-e mojood dar system.

    $ hcitool scan

    🔹 Scan kardan baraye device-haye Bluetooth-e dar hale pakhsh.

    $ hcitool info 00:11:22:33:44:55

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at dar mored device-e Bluetooth ba address-e moshakhas shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hcitool scan

    🔹 Device-haye Bluetooth-e nazdik ra peyda mikonad va address-e MAC va name anha ra namayesh midahad.  Az in etela'at mitavanid baraye vasl shodan be device-haye Bluetooth estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hcitool` command is used to configure Bluetooth connections in Linux.  It allows you to discover Bluetooth devices, connect to them, and view Bluetooth information.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hcitool dev`     --> 💻 Display available Bluetooth devices.
    🔹 `hcitool scan`    --> 📡 Scan for nearby Bluetooth devices.
    🔹 `hcitool info <address>` --> ℹ️ Display information about a Bluetooth device (you must provide the address).
    🔹 `hcitool con`     --> 🔗 Display active Bluetooth connections.
    🔹 `hcitool disconnect <address>` --> 🚫 Disconnect a Bluetooth connection.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hcitool dev

    🔹 Display available Bluetooth devices on the system.

    $ hcitool scan

    🔹 Scan for Bluetooth devices that are advertising.

    $ hcitool info 00:11:22:33:44:55

    🔹 Display information about the Bluetooth device with the specified address.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hcitool scan

    🔹 Discovers nearby Bluetooth devices and displays their MAC addresses and names. This information can then be used to connect to the Bluetooth devices.
